The commissioner shall approve the plan of conversion if the commissioner finds, following the hearing, that the plan of conversion:
Complies with the provisions of this chapter and all other applicable laws;
Is fair and equitable to the eligible members and the other policyholders of the converting mutual;
Is actuarially reasonable and appropriate;
Will not jeopardize the financial stability of the former mutual or prejudice the interest of its policyholders; and
Provides that the former mutual shall be able to satisfy the requirements for issuance of a certificate of authority to write the kinds of insurance for which the converting mutual is presently authorized.
